OL,3,CWhy is the newly elected Speaker of
OL,4,Cthe House of Commons dragged into
OL,5,Cposition?
OL,7,FOn Tuesday, as Sir Lindsay Hoyle was
OL,8,Fre-elected as Speaker, he was
OL,9,Fphysically dragged into position as
OL,10,Fpart of a centuries-old tradition.
OL,12,FBut why does this happen? ITV News
OL,13,FExplains.
OL,15,FWhen did the tradition start?
OL,17,FThe exact origins of the tradition are
OL,18,Fnot known, but it has been a part of
OL,19,Fthe ceremonial proceedings surrounding
OL,20,Fthe election for several centuries.
