OL,3,CWhy is the newly elected Speaker of
OL,4,Cthe House of Commons dragged into
OL,5,Cposition?
OL,7,FHow did the dragging start?
OL,9,FIt has its roots in the original
OL,10,Ffunction of the Speaker which was to
OL,11,Fcommunicate the Commons' opinions to
OL,12,Fthe monarch.
OL,14,FHistorically, if the monarch didn't
OL,15,Fagree with the message being
OL,16,Fcommunicated then they could order the
OL,17,Fdeath of the Speaker.
OL,19,FTherefore previous Speakers required
OL,20,Fsome persuasion to accept the post.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/6
