OL,3,CWhy is the newly elected Speaker of
OL,4,Cthe House of Commons dragged into
OL,5,Cposition?
OL,7,FWhy does it still happen?
OL,9,FThe custom continues to this day as a
OL,10,Fsymbolic gesture and is considered an
OL,11,Fimportant part of the formalities that
OL,12,Faccompany the appointment of a new
OL,13,FSpeaker.
OL,15,FBut the tradition stretches beyond the
OL,16,FUK and around the Commonwealth .
